# ==============================================================================
# REALTIME DATABASE (RTDB) CONFIGURATION for FIREBASE FUNCTIONS
#
# This variable is required by Firebase Functions when interacting with the
# Realtime Database. It specifies the name of the database instance.
#
# CONSTRUCTION: This value is typically formed by taking your
# FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID and appending '-default-rtdb'.
#
# How to find this value:
# 1. Go to your Firebase Project Console and navigate to Project Settings.
# 2. The project ID is found under the 'General' tab (e.g., 'your-project-ewe23r').
# 3. Append '-default-rtdb' to get the instance name.
# ==============================================================================

# Example value: "your-project-ewe23r-default-rtdb"
RTDB_INSTANCE_NAME=""